Currently, when running the `gulp watch` task, a syntax error in
one of the source files causes the watch task to break and the
task has to be cancelled and restarted.

With this update, an error will just terminate the current pipe
but allow the watch task to run properly the next time there are
file changes.

Renamed indexes to avoid collisions in the future.

Renamed all indexes to follow pattern “EXTENSION_TABLE_IDENTIFIER”. This is in order to avoid collisions between extensions using the same index names. In MySQL this doesn’t matter. However, in SQLite the index on a table has to be unique on the database level.
